<i>Posted by Carmaris on 03-23-2003 07:14 AM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>First, gotta say that I hope no one would be so lame as to vote twice if they have two accounts here <img src="/forums/images/smilies/chomp.gif" border="0" alt=""> <br />
<br />
Second, when you get into legal matters, free will only goes so far.  It is ridiculous to have consensual crimes (which is what smoking pot is), but there are laws which fly in the face of free will that make sense in the grander scheme.<br />
<br />
I do believe that marijuana should be legalized, for several reasons.<br />
<br />
1) As Reapin stated, do what you want with your body, I don't care.  Your choice.<br />
<br />
2) Marijuana isn't illegal because it's a drug...well, it is, but there's more to it than that.  Lumber companies played a big part via lobbying to get marijuana illegalized (hehe, is that a word?) in the first place; lumber companies and cotton farmers still lobby to keep it illegal.  Why?  Because 1 acre of hemp can produce as much paper as four acres of trees--imagine what hemp paper would do to the profits of lumber companies!  Because hemp clothing is more durable and cheaper to make than cotton--again, imagine what that would do to cotton farmers!<br />
<br />
3) Marijuana is far less destructive than alcohol, which is legal.  I've never known anyone who beat up their wife and kids, shot someone, got in a bar fight, etc after smoking a couple joints.<br />
<br />
4) The fact that drugs are illegal is what causes most of the problems with them.  You think people would be killing each other if drugs were legal?  No, because they wouldn't be the big money business that they are.  Many kids take drugs because it is illegal--it's a great way to rebel, and it's fun at the same time!  If drugs weren't illegal, more people would be likely to seek help for their addictions--as it is, the social stigma associated with drug users keeps some from getting help they need.<!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_signature -->
