<p>Well to begin with, I'd vote yes for legalization.  Same for prostitution by the way.<br />
<br />
I have to say I find it so funny that people who seem to barely be able to scrape up enough brain cells to remember to breathe, suddenly become Bio-Chemists when talking about pot.  They cant tell you who the current Vice President is, but they'll give a disertation on Hydroponics, THC, absorption into the bloodstream and produce current statistics on the effects of marijuana when you ask them why it should be legal <img src="images/smilies/rolleyes.gif" border="0" alt=""> <br />
<br />
I've seen the arguments on both sides and I happen to think people are doing it anyway... so might as well have it government regulated.  <br />
I'm not a pot smoker, I've experimented maybe 5 times? total.  Personally I never saw what was so great about it.  Yes I inhaled =P  <br />
<br />
Then again I dont drink much either.<br />
<br />
Marijuana is no worse than drinking alcohol IMO, other than the fact that drug cartels are getting rich of the stuff.  <br />
<br />
Have the government regulate it rather than track it down.  Let them take a nice chunk of money from it in taxes.  Obviously same rules as for alcohol.  Age limit, no smoking in public, no driving etc etc etc.<!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_signature -->
